timelineData.title: Crown Black Diamond Ambassador
timelineData.description: An existing Imperial Black Diamond Ambassador must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 200/PCM across all the berth organizations for consecutively 4 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 1,00,000

timelineData.title: Imperial Black Diamond Ambassador
timelineData.description: An existing Royal Black Diamond Ambassador must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 200/PCM across any 4 berth organizations for consecutively 4 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 1,00,000

timelineData.title: Royal Black Diamond Ambassador
timelineData.description: An existing Black Diamond Ambassador must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 200/PCM across any 3 berth organizations for consecutively 4 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 1,00,000

timelineData.title: Black Diamond Ambassador
timelineData.subTitle: current rank
timelineData.description: An existing Executive White Diamond must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 200/PCM across any 2 berth organizations for consecutively 4 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 50,000 as well as MWA (Minimum Weekly Average) of 50,000

timelineData.title: Executive White Diamond
timelineData.description: An existing Executive Purple Diamond must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 200/PCM across any 2 berth organizations for consecutively 3 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 25,000 as well as MWA (Minimum Weekly Average) of 12,500

timelineData.title: Executive Purple Diamond
timelineData.description: An existing Executive Blue Diamond must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 200/PCM across any 2 berth organizations for consecutively 3 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 20,000 as well as MWA (Minimum Weekly Average) of 10,000

timelineData.title: Executive Blue Diamond
timelineData.description: An existing Executive Diamond must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 200/PCM across any 2 berth organizations for consecutively 3 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 15,000 as well as MWA (Minimum Weekly Average) of 7,500

timelineData.title: Executive Diamond
timelineData.subTitle: paid as rank
timelineData.description: An existing Sapphire Executive must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 200/PCM across any 2 berth organizations for consecutively 3 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 10,000 as well as MWA (Minimum Weekly Average) of 5,000

timelineData.title: Sapphire Executive
timelineData.description: An existing Emerald Executive must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 100 across any 2 berth organizations for consecutively 2 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 7,500 as well as MWA (Minimum Weekly Average) of 3,750

timelineData.title: Emerald Executive
timelineData.description: An existing Pearl Executive must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 100 across any 2 berth organizations for consecutively 2 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 5,000 as well as MWA (Minimum Weekly Average) of 2,500

timelineData.title: Pearl Executive
timelineData.description: An existing Ruby Executive must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 50 across any 2 berth organizations for consecutively 2 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 2,500 as well as MWA (Minimum Weekly Average) of 1,250

timelineData.title: Ruby Executive
timelineData.description: An existing Star-1000 must maintain AL (Activity Level) of 50 across any 2 berth organizations for consecutively 2 weeks with GV (Group Volume) of 1,000 as well as MWA (Minimum Weekly Average) of 500

timelineData.title: Star-1000
timelineData.description: An existing Star-500* who has one each active Star-500 in both the organisations and has earned an aggregate income of 1,000 GBU from the date of enrolment.

timelineData.title: Star-500
timelineData.description: An existing Star-250* who has one each active Star-250 on both the organisations and generates 500 GV each from both the organisations in the qualifying week.

timelineData.title: Star-250
timelineData.description: A distributor*/Star* who has one each active personally sponsored Star in both the organisations and generates 250 GV from the lesser side organisation in the qualifying week.

timelineData.title: Star
timelineData.description: A distributor* who has one each active personally sponsored distributors in both the organisations in the qualifying week.
